caption: b"Things we're thankful for this Thanksgiving. 2020 Edition. \nHow about you?"

b"We're here to be your wheels. Take 50% off your ride to vote on Nov. 3 (up to $10) with code 2020VOTE.

#election #election2020

(Terms in bio)"

b'Go to lyft.com/vote (link in bio) to share, download, and print these voting PSAs to remind everyone to get to the polls on Nov 3rd, and take 50% off your ride to vote (up to $10) with code 2020VOTE.

:artist_palette:credit to @lisategtmeier 

(Terms apply).

#ridetovote
#election 
#election2020'

b'5 days until the election is still plenty of time to vote early, drop off your ballot, or plan your ride to vote. Get 50% off your ride to the polls on Nov. 3, up to $10, with code 2020VOTE. \n\nTerms apply (link in bio).'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s 10 days until the election. Which is not enough time to grow an avocado, but it\xe2\x80\x99s still plenty of time to plan your ride to vote. We\xe2\x80\x99re here to be your wheels. And we\xe2\x80\x99ll give you 50% off your ride on Nov. 3, up to $10, with code 2020VOTE. \n\nTerms in bio.'
b'Perks, now with a side of perks. Order up a Lyft Pink membership and get unlimited free delivery with Grubhub+'

b'You have the ride to vote. On November 3, get 50% off one ride up to $10 to any polling location. 

Terms apply (see link in bio)

#vote #vote2020 #lyft'
b'If you\xe2\x80\x99re stuck inside, be stuck inside with food. Live your best life with a Lyft Pink membership and free delivery with Grubhub+'

b'Walk. Run. Bike. Scoot. Skate. Zipline. Paraglide. Scuba dive. Teleport. It doesn\xe2\x80\x99t matter how you get to the polls, but if you need a ride, we\xe2\x80\x99re here to be your wheels. #RideToVote\n\n#vote #vote2020 #election'

b'Time doesn\xe2\x80\x99t exist anymore. On the bright side neither do delivery fees. Your Lyft Pink membership now comes with Grubhub+ unlimited free delivery, and tbh that\xe2\x80\x99s pretty good even by non-2020 standards.'
b'Millions of people lack access to reliable, affordable transportation. We\xe2\x80\x99re partnering with organizations like Bread of Life to help essential workers across the country get to work.'

b'Did you know Lyft is the largest bikeshare operator in the country? This week we added Santa Monica to our family of e-bike towns :party_popper: \n\nThey now ride alongside New York, Chicago, Minneapolis, Columbus, San Francisco, Washington, DC, and Portland :bicycle:'
b"We\xe2\x80\x99re partnering with @michaelbjordan's Outlier Society Fellowship to give access to rides to young professionals like Ariel Laura. Join us. #LyftUp"

b'"We\xe2\x80\x99re all in this world together.\xe2\x80\x9d
- Lyft Driver, Al Smith.

Millions lack access to affordable, reliable transportation. Drivers like Al Smith are helping us change that.'

b"(sound on :speaker_high_volume:) \xe2\x80\x9cVoting is a righteous act for black women. Having rides to the polls is what makes that possible.\xe2\x80\x9d - Cassandra Welchlin of @msblackwomensroundtable Transportation shouldn't be a barrier to having your voice heard."

b"This election day we're offering 50% off a ride up to $10 to any polling location or mail-in dropbox in the country using the code 2020VOTE. And for the first time ever, this offer applies to our network of bikes and scooters! :ballot_box_with_ballot_selector::automobile::bicycle::kick_scooter: \nLINK IN BIO"

b":police_car_light:UPDATE: We're still rolling in California \xe2\x80\x94 for now. \n\nA court has granted our request for a stay. This means we can keep rideshare in California for all the drivers & riders who depend on it. A big thank you to everyone who urged California to keep our service going! Ride on. :automobile:"
b'Millions of people lack access to affordable, reliable transportation. Join us in helping close opportunity gaps. #lyftup (Link in bio)'

b"More than 15,000 New Yorkers came together with @citibike and @streetridersnyc in solidarity against racial injustice. 

To help keep this movement going, we're sponsoring solidarity ride participants all month long. #BlackLivesMatter. 
 
:round_pushpin: Times Square, NYC
:camera_with_flash:: @tobytenenbaum"

b'\xe2\x81\xa3It\xe2\x80\x99s a beautiful day to scoot around downtown :kick_scooter::dog:! Or take a walk. Did somebody say walk? #scootlyfe\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
:round_pushpin:: D.C.\xe2\xa0\x80
:camera_with_flash:: Sasha Slacum'

b'Over the last few weeks, we\xe2\x80\x99ve witnessed what can happen when spaces that used to be defined by cars are repurposed for something more impactful \xe2\x80\x94 canvases to amplify the #BlackLivesMatter movement, open spaces to congregate in solidarity, and a place to reimagine a better future for our cities. \xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s beautiful to see so many people fearlessly standing up for what is right. Personally, as a Black man in America, I didn't think so many people would even care and I am thankful for every bit of support that the movement is receiving,\xe2\x80\x9d says Demetris "BAMR" Washington, the artist behind Sacramento\xe2\x80\x99s Black Lives Matter grass mural.

Thank you to @bamr_theartist for leading this mural initiative, and allowing us to share this incredible work with the Lyft community.

b'When we listen, we can find the courage and inspiration to make change happen. Meet Crystal Ferguson: author, podcast host, activist, and Lyft driver in Brooklyn, NY. A champion of the #BlackLivesMatter movement, Crystal uses her voice to motivate and inspire each of us to find ways to lift each other up. Thank you @chryssiej_ for allowing us to share your story. \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80

b'Starting this year, we\xe2\x80\x99re making Juneteenth an official holiday at Lyft. It\xe2\x80\x99s one step in our ongoing journey toward racial equality at Lyft, and in this country.'
b'A note from our co-founders: a call to action for each of us. (Link in bio)'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cIt feels so good to \xe2\x80\xa6 make nourishing meals for our fellow humans who are putting their lives on the line,\xe2\x80\x9d says Silvan Harlap, Owner of Eastwood in NYC.\n\nWe\xe2\x80\x99re teaming up with @SonderStays and @offtheirplate to provide free ride credit to restaurant workers around the US so they can get to their jobs, where they\xe2\x80\x99re  prepping food for healthcare workers. #LyftUp More details at link in bio.'

b'Sometimes, a little back seat karaoke session is all it takes to feel like a firework. :sparkles: Check out #TheLovebirds :sparkling_heart::dove_selector: this weekend on @netflixfilm for a pick-me-up!'

b'One of our favorite things, you ask? Seeing pics of healthcare workers using their free bikeshare memberships to get to work. \nKeep the pics coming! Tag @Lyft and @Citibike in your photos. #LyftUp #ReservedforHeroes (:camera:: @volpad5)'

b'@ChefJJ, founder and chef of @FieldTripHarlem, is donating over 4000 meals a week to NYC\xe2\x80\x99s essential workforce and families in need, all of them delivered via Lyft drivers. Thanks to our Driver Task Force for making these deliveries possible. #LyftUp'

b'Through LyftUp, we\xe2\x80\x99re working to make sure everyone has access to affordable, reliable transportation. \nAlong with @uninterrupted and @kingjames, we\xe2\x80\x99re celebrating graduates with free bikeshare memberships to graduating students across the country this fall. #lyftup #classof2020 (Link in bio) :camera:: January 2020'
b'For the communities most impacted by COVID-19, a ride can make all the difference. Our #LyftUp alliance of over 500 partners is expanding transportation access to those who need it most right now.'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s been a rough couple of weeks. Take a minute to smile at something cute today. Like this dog riding a scooter.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThese daily rides became my mental health break,\xe2\x80\x9d says C\xc3\xa9sar Fern\xc3\xa1dez-Chav\xc3\xa9z, Head of the Language Department at Mt. Sinai Beth Israel. He\xe2\x80\x99s been using Citi Bike to get to and from the hospital. \xe2\x80\x9cI have been working very tirelessly making sure our technology is ready to help healthcare providers communicate with patients who don\xe2\x80\x99t speak English.\xe2\x80\x9d
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
We\xe2\x80\x99re happy to provide free, one-year Citi Bike memberships to all the healthcare workers out there uplifting their communities \xe2\x80\x94 like C\xc3\xa9sar.\xc2\xa0#ReservedforHeroes\xc2\xa0#LyftUp (:camera_with_flash::\xc2\xa0@cefecha)'

b'Girl Scout Troop 3743 made care packages for healthcare workers by hand. (Yes, they include #GirlScoutCookies.) We were happy to help deliver them, contact-free. Thanks to @GirlScouts for reminding us all to take care of ourselves. #LyftUp'

b'Drivers are now picking up :red_apple::green_salad::baguette_bread:+ :hospital: and dropping them off to people in need, with Essential Deliveries. Thanks to everyone driving for their communities. #LyftUp'

b'Big :bicycle: news: @CitiBike is giving a free year of membership to more essential workers across NYC. :raising_hands:

Huge thanks to @NYCMayor, @NYC_DOT, @citi, @mastercard, for coming together to help those who are helping NYC. :blue_heart:

Check the link in bio for more info and enrollment details #ReservedForHeroes #LyftUp (:camera_with_flash:: @lousyjerk)'

b'Together with over 120,000 members of the driver community, we formed a Driver Task Force to provide rides to those who need it most. Thanks to those helping deliver essential supplies, food, and rides for front-line medical professionals #LyftUp. Join us at Lyft.com/lyftup'
b'Find out how we\xe2\x80\x99re helping communities across America at the link in our bio. #LyftUp'

b'@friendssocal provides mentoring, essentials, and food for families affected by foster care across LA. It\xe2\x80\x99s a mission Lyft is proud to support by funding free rides for those families in a deeply impacted city. #lyftup'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re thankful for the driver community for all that they do to help one another. In New England, Lyft Driver Advisory Council members Leon and Damion pitched in, helping to distribute hand sanitizer and snacks to drivers.\n\nKnow a driver who deserves a shout out? Let us know in the comments below! :backhand_index_pointing_down:'

b'LyftUp has created a network of over 500 partners to offer access to free transportation for vulnerable communities, critical workers, and critical supplies. We\xe2\x80\x99re in this together. Join us at lyft.com/lyftup (link in bio) #LyftUp'

b'Thank you to everyone on the front lines doing their part to uplift their communities during this time.

Thank you to the transit operators.
Thank you to the medical workers & first responders.
Thank you to the grocery clerks & restockers.
Thank you to the delivery people.
Thank you to everyone working in the food industry.
Thank you to the Lyft drivers.

Know a driver who deserves recognition? Let us know in the comments. :backhand_index_pointing_down: (:artist_palette:: @harmonywillowart)'

b"Running low on essentials? We hear there's a driver in Salt Lake City who's got their riders covered :roll_of_paper: .\n\nWho else has met a driver or rider helping out with the essentials? Drop your story in the comments. :backhand_index_pointing_down:"

b'Thank you to all the drivers on the road who continue to provide rides for essential needs. To support the health and safety of the community, we\xe2\x80\x99re distributing free hand sanitizer and other cleaning supplies to Lyft drivers :automobile::round_pushpin:. \xe2\x80\xa2\n\xe2\x80\xa2\nLink in bio for more info on how we\xe2\x80\x99re helping drivers during this crucial time, including info about socially distant sanitizer distribution at select Hubs.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI picked up a doctor from the 32nd navy base and dropped him off to the Navy hospital. I was about to call it quits early but this guy needed a ride to the hospital to work. Everybody\xe2\x80\x99s got to do their part,\xe2\x80\x9d says Lyft driver, Frank.\n\nWhether your part is staying home or helping essential workers do their jobs, thank you to all of you for looking out for our communities. Know someone else making a difference? Let us know in the comments :backhand_index_pointing_down:'

b"First responders, transit workers, and the healthcare workforce are vital to our community at this time. We want to make sure it's easy for these critical workers to get where they need to go. With our friends\xc2\xa0@citibike, we're helping to connect them to convenient transportation. :bicycle::person_biking::bicycle::woman_biking_selector::bicycle::dashing_away: .\n\nLink in bio for more information."

b'"A small act of goodness and kindness can make a difference" -Seattle driver, Eli, delivering donated masks from businesses to local hospitals in need. Know a Lyft driver or rider doing good in your community? Let us know in the comments! :backhand_index_pointing_down:'

b'We know Lyft can be a critical lifeline for communities in need. Many people still need help reaching essential services, and many drivers count on this work for extra income. We\xe2\x80\x99re taking immediate action to help with both. Check the link in our bio to learn more about our community initiatives, and how you can help.'

b"If you didn't scoot to your wedding like @morais4 and @maryelizabethh5, did you really get married??? jk we love love, but srsly, scooters + weddings = joy :two_hearts::kick_scooter:! (:camera_with_flash:: @thetinyweddingshop)"

b'TBH, we\xe2\x80\x99ve had @justinbieber\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x99ETA\xe2\x80\x99 song on repeat ever since his new #Changes album dropped!\n\nEnter Promo code WHATSYOURETA in the #Lyft app for a chance to win tickets to the upcoming #ChangesTour AND a free year of Lyft rides, on us. #ETA NO PURCH NEC. USA; 18+. Rules in bio. :raising_hands::musical_notes:'

b"We're so lucky we get to share these loving moments with you guyssss. :growing_heart: Congrats to @jennymaier and @thedenuch for tying the knot (and using #Lyft to get there!) :bride_with_veil::man_in_tuxedo::automobile::dashing_away:"

b'When people get into a #Lyft driven by 5-Star Dallas native Wanda, it\xe2\x80\x99s impossible not to see how much we all have in common. We took a ride with Wanda and learned about the power of being accepted for who you are. :sparkles:'
b"We get it, Mondays can be ruff. But we'll tail you what, here's a cute dog photo to help get you through the week. (:camera_with_flash:: @keepingupwithbiff, :dog_face:: @biffthesamoyed)"

b'The George Washington Bridge sees half a million cyclists and pedestrians every year, and there are initiatives in place to make biking and walking across the bridge even safer and easier. \nWe\xe2\x80\x99re here for that. The more bikeable our cities become, the more sustainable our cities can be. Big :clapping_hands::clapping_hands::clapping_hands::clapping_hands::clapping_hands: to the GW Bridge for being part of the future.  #StreetstoSee (:camera_with_flash:: @tobyharriman)'

b'Watch Grammy-winning @AliciaKeys take the :key:s and give some lucky Angelenos #Lyft rides in this special edition of Undercover Lyft. Your favorite New Yorker is owning LA traffic and dropping a :hot_pepper: collab with passenger @mxrceloxarcxngel.\n\nWant to ride like a rockstar for your community? Join #LyftUp :automobile::sparkles::flexed_biceps: (Link in bio.)'

b':speaking_head: Hey @Chase Sapphire Reserve cardmembers, ICYMI you guys get 10x total points through March 2022 when you ride with #Lyft. OH and you also get a free year of Lyft Pink. :raising_hands: #winning\n\nLearn more: https://lft.to/2UerVjt #ChaseSapphire'

b"If we launched #Lyft in the largest North American city without ridesharing and didn't throw a party to celebrate, did we really launch? #LyftVancouver\n\nExcited to now be live in #Vancouver and support the amazing work of the @TeganAndSaraFoundation. :musical_notes::guitar::automobile:"

b"Millions lack access to basic human needs because they can't get a ride. We brought #LyftUp to @sundanceorg with programming in our #lyftlounge to help spread awareness around transportation access :growing_heart:.
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
Join us. Link in bio. (:camera_with_flash:: @tutes)"

b"It's more than just a bike \xe2\x80\x94 it's an epic love. :two_hearts::bicycle: What's your bike story? #StartedWithaBike #LyftUp
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
:camera_with_flash:: @nigelsylvester"
b'Lyft in #Vancouver. You love :growing_heart: to see it. (:camera_with_flash:: @romanlanon)'

b'Whether you were riding solo, cruising with the squad, rocking Grandma\xe2\x80\x99s beach cruiser or doing tricks on a scraper bike, it was more than a bike \xe2\x80\x94 it was a way of life. What\xe2\x80\x99s your bike story? Share it and tag #StartedWithaBike #lyftup :bicycle::raising_hands:'

b'We teamed up with the Harlem Y to host a community event for 50 young people \xe2\x80\x94 with a surprise visit from @KingJames. They\xe2\x80\x99ll be the first of thousands of young people across the country to get one-year bikeshare memberships as a part of #LyftUp.\n\nLearn more. Link in bio.'

b'ICYMI: @KingJames made a surprise visit to our event at the Harlem @YMCANYC to talk about the difference a bike can make in a young person\xe2\x80\x99s life. A bike can take you all the way to whoever you want to be. But first, you need access to that bike. #LyftUp :bicycle::dashing_away:'

b'For @KingJames, it all started with a bike. \xe2\x80\x9cIt was more than a way to go see my friends or play basketball \xe2\x80\x94 it was a way of life. A bike opened doors, allowed me to get to safe places after school, and gave me access to opportunities I never would have known.\xe2\x80\x9d
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
We\xe2\x80\x99re partnering with Lebron James and @uninterrupted to give one-year bikeshare memberships to thousands of young people across the country. :bicycle::dashing_away: Join us. Link in bio.'
b'San Francisco, biking up those hills just got way easier. :bicycle::high_voltage:Zoom into the weekend with our newly returned ebikes!'

b'Hop in, Bad Boys! And watch the OG himself @WillSmith take a joyride with some lucky #Lyft riders through the mean streets of Miami. Didn\xe2\x80\x99t catch your ride with Will? You can get in on the action TODAY with #BadBoysForLife \xe2\x80\x94 now in theaters. :smiling_face_with_sunglasses::automobile::collision::clapper_board::popcorn:'

b"Celebrity hairstylist turned five-star #Lyft driver, Jackee White has given over 20,000 rides and counting! :flexed_biceps: Check out our story to learn more about @celebrities_atl's experience being a top female driver in Atlanta. (:camera:: @patrickkolts)"
b'Looking forward to the new year ahead, filled with endless pawsibilities :dog_face:. (:camera:: @lilmanlife)'

b'Our co-founder John Zimmer rang in 2020 the way he does every year: driving on NYE:smiling_face_with_sunglasses::automobile::dashing_away:! \xe2\x81\xa3\n\xe2\x81\xa3\nFrom all of us at\xe2\x80\x8b #\xe2\x80\x8bLyft\xe2\x80\x8b, thanks to our driver community for helping people get home safely last night.'
